parties.raw_snippet:
This Content License Agreement ("Agreement"), dated as of Feb 10, 2014 (the "Effective Date"), is by and between PSiTech Corporation, a BVI
Corporation, with offices located at 303, 3rdFl, St. Georges Bldg, 2 Ice House St, Central, Hong Kong("Licensor"), and Empirical Ventures, Inc., a
Nevada corporation with offices located at 100, 40 Lake Bellevue Dr, Bellevue, WA("Licensee").
parties.reasoning: The sentence explicitly names the two contracting parties and identifies their roles (Licensor and Licensee). It appears at the beginning of the agreement where parties are typically identified.

contract_type.reasoning: The agreement's title and substance center on licensing content for display on Licensee's website and related media, with payment of license fees and royalties and trademark use rules. The primary subject is the grant of rights to use Licensed Content and Marks, which makes this a license agreement.

agreement_date.reasoning: The phrase 'dated as of' directly states when the agreement was made/signed; it appears in the opening sentence defining the Effective Date.

effective_date.reasoning: The opening sentence defines 'Effective Date' and ties it to Feb 10, 2014, so the Effective Date equals the agreement date.

expiration_date.raw_snippet:
The initial term of this Agreement commences as of the Effective Date and, unless terminated earlier pursuant to any express provision
of this Agreement, shall continue until five (5) years following the Effective Date (the "Initial Term").
expiration_date.reasoning: Section 6.1 sets the initial duration as continuing 'until five (5) years following the Effective Date' which is a relative expiration/term description.
expiration_date.normalized_value: five (5) years following the Effective Date

governing_law.raw_snippet: This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the internal laws of the State of Nevada without giving effect to any choice or conflict of law provision or rule.
governing_law.reasoning: Section 11.11 contains the governing law clause and explicitly identifies the State of Nevada as the governing jurisdiction.

notice_period.raw_snippet: Thereafter, this Agreement shall renew automatically for one (1) additional three (3) year period (the "Renewal Term" and collectively, together with the Initial Term, the "Term") unless either party provides the other with written notice of non-renewal at least ninety (90) days before the expiration of the Initial Term].
notice_period.reasoning: This sentence in Section 6.1 specifies the advance written notice period required to prevent automatic renewal ('at least ninety (90) days before the expiration of the Initial Term'). That is the notice-to-prevent-renewal period requested.

renewal_term.raw_snippet: Thereafter, this Agreement shall renew automatically for one (1) additional three (3) year period (the "Renewal Term" and collectively, together with the Initial Term, the "Term")
renewal_term.reasoning: Section 6.1 states the contract will automatically renew for 'one (1) additional three (3) year period' after the initial term, which defines the renewal term.
